description:
Josylvio komt met een gek album binnenkort en gaat langs bij Rotjoch met een paar beats van OG Vibez. Die hiphop-shit op je beeldscherm!

https://www.bnnvara.nl/101barz/artikelen/artikel-josylvio-brengt-klassieke-sessies 

#JOSYLVIO #ZOMERSESSIE #101BARZ

Mixed & Mastered by Rawbeem

101Barz is het grootste hiphop-platform van Nederland met wekelijks nieuwe video's. Natuurlijk brengt Rotjoch elke week de welbekende studiosessies op je beeldscherm, maar dat is niet alles. We gaan langs bij producers en zien hoe zij een beat maken voor de beginnende artiesten thuis in de serie 'BPM'. We zoeken talenten op in hun eigen buurt om ze beter te leren kennen in 'Talent vd Maand'. Ben je op zoek naar wat langere interviews? Dan is onze serie 'Ins & Outs' iets voor jou.

Is ons YouTube-kanaal niet genoeg? Onze redactie houdt de website voor jullie up to date! Wekelijks nieuwe releases in een overzichtelijke lijst, achtergrond informatie bij de nieuwe sessies, stemmen op de #TBT... Ga naar 101barz.nl.

http://101barz.nl

Wil jij de redactie iets mailen? Stuur het naar info@101Barz.nl

In 2006 had Rotjoch het idee om onder de vleugel van BNN het hiphopplatform 101Barz op te zetten. Rappers kwamen langs voor studiosessies en binnen de kortste keren was 101Barz een begrip in Nederland.  Welke bekende rapper begon niet zijn carriÃ¨re bij 101Barz?

Oscar  nominee  Denis  Villeneuve  (â€œArrival,â€  â€œBlade  Runner  2049â€)  directs  Warner  Bros.  Pictures  and  Legendary Picturesâ€™ â€œDune,â€ the big-screen adaptation of Frank Herbertâ€™s seminal bestseller of the same name. A mythic and emotionally charged heroâ€™s journey, â€œDuneâ€ tells the story of Paul Atreides, a brilliant and gifted young man born into a great destiny beyond his understanding, who must travel to the most dangerous planet  in  the  universe  to  ensure  the  future  of  his  family  and  his  people.  As  malevolent  forces  explode  into conflict over the planetâ€™s exclusive supply of the most precious resource in existenceâ€”a commodity capable of unlocking humanityâ€™s greatest potentialâ€”only those who can conquer their fear will survive.The film stars Oscar nominee TimothÃ©e Chalamet (â€œCall Me by Your Name,â€  â€œLittle Womenâ€), Rebecca Ferguson  (â€œStephen  Kingâ€™s  Doctor  Sleep,â€   â€œMission:  Impossible  â€“  Falloutâ€),  Oscar  Isaac  (the â€œStar  Warsâ€ franchise) Oscar nominee Josh Brolin (â€œMilk,â€ â€œAvengers: Infinity Warâ€), Stellan SkarsgÃ¥rd (HBOâ€™s â€œChernobyl,â€ â€œAvengers: Age of Ultronâ€), Dave Bautista (the â€œGuardians of the Galaxyâ€ films, â€œAvengers: Endgameâ€), Stephen McKinley Henderson (â€œFences,â€ â€œLady Birdâ€), Zendaya (â€œSpider-Man: Homecoming,â€ HBOâ€™s â€œEuphoriaâ€), Chang Chen (â€œMr.  Long,â€ â€œCrouching  Tiger,  Hidden  Dragonâ€),    David  Dastmalchian  (â€œBlade  Runner  2049,â€  â€œThe  Dark  Knightâ€), Sharon  Duncan-Brewster  (â€œRogue  One:  A  Star  Wars  Story,â€  Netflixâ€™s â€œSex  Educationâ€),   with  Oscar  nominee Charlotte Rampling (â€œ45 Years,â€ â€œAssassinâ€™s Creedâ€), with Jason Momoa (â€œAquaman,â€ HBOâ€™s â€œGame of Thronesâ€), and Oscar winner Javier Bardem (â€œNo Country for Old Men,â€ â€œSkyfallâ€).   Villeneuve directed â€œDuneâ€ from a screenplay he co-wrote with Jon Spaihts and Eric Roth based on the novel of the same name written by Frank Herbert. Gains, Jon Spaihts, Thomas Tull, Brian Herbert, Byron Merritt and Kim Herbert. He  also  collaborated  for  the  first  time  with  Oscar-nominated  director  of  photography  Greig  Fraser  (â€œLion,â€  â€œZero  Dark  Thirty,â€  â€œRogue  One:  A  Star  Wars  Storyâ€);  three-time  Oscar-nominated  costume  designer  
Jacqueline West (â€œThe Revenant,â€ â€œThe Curious Case of Benjamin Button,â€ â€œQuillsâ€) and co-costume designer Bob Morgan; and stunt coordinator Tom Struthers (â€œThe Dark Knightâ€ trilogy, â€œInceptionâ€).  Oscar-winning and multiple  Oscar-nominated  composer  Hans  Zimmer  (â€œBlade  Runner  2049,â€  â€œInception,â€  â€œGladiator,â€  â€œThe  Lion Kingâ€) is creating the score.  Warner  Bros.  Pictures  and  Legendary  Pictures  Present  â€œDune.â€    The  film  is  slated  to  be  released  in  theaters on December 18, 2020.

video_title: Plushie Makeover: First Time Custom With NerdECrafter
tags: squishy makeover|custom plushies|custom figures|custom collectibles|cool things to customize
description:
Hey guys! Today is a super exciting nw project, I've NEVER seen anyone do this before, Jackie from NerdEcrafter and I have decided to try customizing plushies for the first time. This is a lot like squishy makeovers, but with plushies instead!

Since this has never been done before, we are having to get very experimental. I ended up using a combination of techniques and materials to give my plushie a makeover. I will be doing some basic sewing, gluing, using felt, ribbon, and lots of fabric paint as usual! We decided to us Squishmallows to customize since they are so simple and really cute. Get ready for some cute plushie creations ğŸ˜Š 

WATCH JACKIE'S VIDEO: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cpG-Q7J48DY&feature=youtu.be&ab_channel=NerdECrafter


___________WELCOME TO MY CHANNEL__________

Hey! my name is Moriah (pronounced muh-rye-yuh ğŸ˜‚ ) and this is my channel....obviously. I'm 25 and like doing anything creative...and being snarky.....just a lil. I make a lot of decorating and painting videos here. I'm obsessed with editing and adding lil bits to my videos, so if that's not your thing....oof you may hate this haha. I paint on squishies, thrift store finds, and other random things I pick up. I also love to draw, but don't expect anything too skilled, I'm not the best at that haha. You will also find occasional crafting/testing crafting kits on my channel which are always a hot mess. And even some baking (REALLY bad at that, but it's fun to try LOL). 

CURRENT SERIES:
Squishy Makeovers: Fixing and decorating used squishies sent from my viewers

video_title: HIGHLIGHTS | Fulham vs Arsenal (0-3) | Willian, Gabriel impress on debuts
tags: Arsenal|Arsenal FC|Arsenal Football Club|Football|Club|EPL|Premier League|Soccer|Sport|Team|aubameyang|lacazette|bernd leno|torreira|guendouzi|ozil|bellerin|hector bellerin|dani Ceballos|Kieran Tierney|reiss nelson|joe Willock|granit xhaka|rob holding|calum chambers|gabriel martinelli|bukayo saka|arsenal vs fulham|arsenal highlights|willian|aubameyang goals|william saliba|gabriel Magalhaes|gabriel|arsenal vs|mo elneny|maitland-niles|emi martinez
description:
We got off to a flying start in the Premier League with a classy performance and three points at Craven Cottage.

Alex Lacazette, debutant Gabriel and Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang were on target while the outstanding Willian claimed two assists on his first appearance for us.

Fulham were bright in the opening moments and a misjudgement from Gabriel almost let in Aboubakar Kamara. Bernd Leno did well to claw the ball off his toes.

From then on, the home side could not live with our pace, movement and quality.

The first goal was a scrappy one. Mohamed Elneny found Aubameyang and his cutback was fired goalwards by Granit Xhaka. Tim Ream failed to clear, Willian reacted first to force a save from Marek Rodak and Lacazette tucked away the rebound.

Willian struck a free-kick against the base of a post with Rodak beaten, and Aubameyang almost scored from a trademark burst in behind the defence in the left-hand channel.

Gabriel grew in stature as the game unfolded and he marked his debut with a downward header to convert Willian's corner. That effectively put the match to bed very early in the second half.

After that it was a matter of how many we would score, and Aubameyang got the third and final goal thanks to a delightful crossfield pass from Willian and one of the captain's sumptuous finishes into the far corner.

There will be tougher tests ahead, but this was a hugely-encouraging start to the new campaign.

video_title: I Tried Acrylic Pour Art For The First Time
tags: I tried acrylic pour art for the first time|acrylic pour art|acrylic fluid art|I tried acrylic pour art|I tried acrylic fluid art|tiktus|tiktus color art|acrylic paint|acrylic|paint pouring|acrylic paint pouring|Safiya art|Safiya paint|Safiya and Tyler|Safiya Nygaard|safia|Safiya|oddly satisfying|visual asmr|art|paint|swirl technique with 5 colors
description:
Hello friends! Apologies for the long absence, but we are trying to get things back on track. No, this video didnâ€™t take us 3 months to make - we filmed a bunch of videos in July and this is the first of them to be released! Itâ€™s not a magnum opus, just supposed to be fun and lighthearted. If you want to read more about our plans, you can check out my blog post here:

https://www.safiyasnewintrosong.com/single-post/2020/09/04/where-have-we-been

Now, onto the video! A few weeks ago, somewhere deep in a visual ASMR YouTube rabbit hole, I discovered the online acrylic pour art community - where people essentially make interesting color combos of paint in a cup, then pour that cup onto a canvas or object - and then manipulate that object to create truly mesmerizing, rainbow, psychedelic pieces of art. And I was instantly hooked - just something about the way the paints flow from the cup and then slide around the canvas really got me, ya know? So I decided to pick an acrylic pour art video and try to follow it myself, to see if I could do it too. So I chose a  pouring guru , Tiktus color art, and got to work.

What do you guys think of my ~acrylic pouring adventure~?

This video is NOT sponsored!!

Safiya's Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/safiyany/
Twitter: https://twitter.com/safiyajn
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/safnygaard/

The tutorial we followed is here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yndPwAMGEgg
You can check out Tiktusâ€™s channel here: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCeAvBShy5a2_vTFflQG_zWg

Hope For The Day (HFTD) is a non-profit movement empowering the conversation on proactive suicide prevention and mental health education. Join the Proactive Suicide Prevention conversation at http://www.hftd.org 

Suicide Prevention starts with a conversation we're not having with our mental health due to Stigma. The first step to breaking that silence is dispelling stigmas of fear, judgement, and shame about our internal experiences. We achieve that by proclaiming It's Ok Not To Be Ok!
